                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13491318" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 6 Nov 2012 08:43:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Trivial patch attached&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13498171" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 15 Nov 2012 17:55:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How about we remove this server-side, but add it to cqlsh?  (Maybe even cut it down to 1K rows there.)  That would address my worries about OOMing the server adequately.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13498172" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 15 Nov 2012 17:56:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(that is: if querystring does not contain &lt;tt&gt;limit&lt;/tt&gt;, cqlsh could add on &lt;tt&gt;LIMIT 1000&lt;/tt&gt; as a default.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13498745" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 16 Nov 2012 11:36:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m clearly fine with that, though while the server-side patch is attached, I&apos;d rather let the cqlsh part to someone that knows the cqlsh code better if possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13500127" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 19 Nov 2012 10:25:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 then.  Created &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4972&quot; title=&quot;Move &amp;quot;add a default limit&amp;quot; logic to cqlsh&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4972&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4972&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for the cqlsh change.  (Would like to get that into 1.2.0 but it&apos;s not critical.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13500372" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 19 Nov 2012 16:57:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Alright, committed, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
